Ellie Parker began as a 16-millimeter short that was screened at the 2001
Sundance Film Festival. Using a handheld digital camera, writer-director
Scott Coffey expanded it into a feature-length film over the next four years.

A hilarious comic portrait of a young woman&#039;s struggle for integrity,
happiness and a Hollywood acting career.

Ellie Parker(Naomi Watts) races around town from one audition to another,
changing make-up, clothes and personality. She speeds along, barely attending to
her whirlwind life as she strives to get cast in a movie.

What happens when you become the person you pretend to be?

One last insane audition for Ellie, and she?s back in the game ...or is she?
